### Important Note

All tests on third-party domains will be performed only with written authorization from the owner; no exploitation or DDoS tests will be executed against third parties.

## Development Guidelines

- Use Bun as package manager (not npm/yarn)
- Follow Next.js 16 App Router conventions
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Apply Tailwind CSS for styling
- Run linting before build: `bun run lint && next build`
- Respect robots.txt and rate limits in all automated scans
- Never execute destructive tests or exploitation without explicit authorization
- All security testing must be non-destructive and respectful
- Maintain clear separation between passive reconnaissance and active testing

## Code Style

- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Follow ESLint configuration (eslint-config-next)
- Use functional components with React 19
- Prefer async/await over promises
- Implement proper error handling for all API calls
- Include proper type definitions for all functions and components
- Screaming arquitecture

